First, we'll use the relation between gcd and lcm:
$\text{lcm}(a, 40) \cdot \gcd(a, 40) = a \cdot 40$

Substituting h₁ and h₂:
$(x \cdot (x + 3)) \cdot (x + 3) = a \cdot 40$
$x \cdot (x + 3)^2 = 40a$

