- $x = 2$: $\gcd(a, 40) = 5$, $\text{lcm}(a, 40) = 10$
  - $\gcd(a, 40) = 5 \implies a$ divisible by 5, not by 2
  - $\text{lcm}(a, 40) = 10 \implies a$ divides 10
  - Divisors of 10: 1, 2, 5, 10
